SIMPLE: lined
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: lined
<hw>lined</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>furnished with items in
a line or as if in a line.</def> <note>Often used in hyphenated form,
prefixed by the item arranged in a line; <as>as, tree-<ex>lined</ex>
streets</as>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>having visible lines; -- used especially of skin;
<as>as, their <ex>lined</ex> faces were immeasurably sad</as>.
Contrasted to <ant>smooth</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> furrowed, seamed.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>having a lining or a liner; often used in
combination; <as>as, a <ex>lined</ex> skirt; a silk-<ex>lined</ex>
jacket</as>. Opposite of <ant>unlined</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>linelike</ent>⟦br⟧
